• Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom and three key trade unions will today resume stalled wage negotiations. The power utility has been engaged in wage negotiations for a number of weeks. Trade union Solidarity said it is expecting to reach a wage settlement with Eskom on Tuesday. READ: Eskom, unions stalemate wage negotiations The unions have asked Public Enterprise Minister Pravin Gordhan and Finance Minister Nhlanhla Nene to sit in during the negotiations. They have also taken the latest offer of 7.5 percent for this year back to their members. eNCA